snippet.textDisplay:
Jeff looks like he lost some weight, which is commendable at his age, if that is so. He says he will be "different," so hopefully we'll have a heel run, or hopefully one or two more championships. With Matt gone, his creative direction can give him more spotlight before he eventually retires, and a heel run with provide the perfect excuse for him to not be the suicidal daredevil that he's has been throughout his whole career. I wouldn't mind seeing a sober 'Anti-christ of professional wrestling,' although with this being the WWE and the kiddos and mindless consumers getting spoonfed whatever is on Vince's weekly menu, my hopes are not high for that. Hopefully he just gets used well.

We have Morrison, AJ Styles, Daniel Bryan, and some other good talent for him to work with, and if he's just gonna come back merely to show off some more face paint, then it's not even worth it. He can go home, enjoy his beautiful family and other artistic endeavors while fading off into that well-earned, long-awaited Hall of Fame.
